react4j.annotations

Annotation Type View


  • @Documented
 @Target(value=TYPE)
public @interface View
    Annotation used to identify a React4j view.

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      Feature inject
      Enum controlling whether javax.inject integration is generated for the view.
      String name
      Return the name of the view.
      Feature sting
      Enum controlling whether Sting injection integration is generated for the view.
      View.Type type
      Enum indicating the capabilities of the view.

    • Element Detail

      • name

        @Nonnull
public abstract String name
        Return the name of the view. The value defaults to the simple name name of the class. If the value is specified, the value must conform to the requirements of a java identifier. It should also be unique across the suite of views used within an application but this is not strictly required as the name is only used for development purposes. (i.e. This is the name that is used within the React DevTools).
        Returns:
        the name of the view.
        Default:
        "<default>"

      • type

        @Nonnull
public abstract View.Type type
        Enum indicating the capabilities of the view. See the View.Type enum for further details.
        Returns:
        an enum indicating the capabilities of the view.
        See Also:
        View.Type
        Default:
        react4j.annotations.View.Type.STATEFUL

      • inject

        public abstract Feature inject
        Enum controlling whether javax.inject integration is generated for the view. The generated class is the same name as the view with the "Factory" suffix. React4j only supports constructor injection and thus this MUST NOT be set to Feature.ENABLE unless there are constructor parameters on the view. If the value is set to Feature.AUTODETECT then the feature will be enabled if the view has constructor parameters and the javax.inject.Inject class is present when compiling the view.
        Returns:
        an enum controlling whether javax.inject integration is generated for the view.
        Default:
        react4j.annotations.Feature.AUTODETECT

      • sting

        public abstract Feature sting
        Enum controlling whether Sting injection integration is generated for the view. The generated class is the same name as the view with the "Factory" suffix. React4j only supports constructor injection and thus this MUST NOT be set to Feature.ENABLE unless there are constructor parameters on the view. If the value is set to Feature.AUTODETECT then the feature will be enabled if the view has constructor parameters and the sting.Injectable class is present when compiling the view.
        Returns:
        an enum controlling whether sting integration is generated for the view.
        Default:
        react4j.annotations.Feature.AUTODETECT
